* {{ill|Okanoue Shrine (Itano)|ja|岡上神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (おかのうえじんじゃ) - A {{ill|Shinto shrine|ja|神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}} located in {{ill|Itano Town|ja|板野町|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Itano District|ja|板野郡|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Tokushima Prefecture|ja|徳島県|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. * {{ill|Okagami Shrine (Kawasaki City)|ja|岡上神社 (川崎市)|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (おかがみじんじゃ) - A Shinto shrine located at 809 Okagami, {{ill|Asao Ward|ja|麻生区|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Kawasaki City|ja|川崎市|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Kanagawa Prefecture|ja|神奈川県|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.<ref>[https://www.kanagawa-jinja.or.jp/search_dtl.php4?jid=95&cd=1201095&scd=&npg=0 Okagami Shrine (おかがみじんじゃ)] Kanagawa Prefecture Shrine Association</ref><ref name="Asao Tourism"/> ** {{ill|Deities|ja|祭神|qq=draft|qq=draft}}: {{ill|Yamato Takeru|ja|日本武尊|1=Yamato Takeru|lt=Prince Yamato Takeru|3=ヤマトタケル|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Takeminakata-no-Kami|ja|建御名方命|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Ōyamakui-no-Kami|ja|大山咋神|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Ukanomitama-no-Mikoto|ja|倉稲魂命|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.<ref name="Asao Tourism"/> ** In 1909 (Meiji 42), five local shrines in {{ill|Okagami Village|ja|岡上村|qq=draft|qq=draft}} were merged under the name "Okagami Shrine." The site of the former {{ill|Suwa Shrine|ja|諏訪神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}} in the center of the village was chosen for the new shrine to promote unity among villagers.<ref name="Asao Tourism">[https://asao-kankou.jp/?page_id=1992 Okagami Shrine (おかがみじんじゃ)] Asao Tourism, Kawasaki/Asao Tourism Association, accessed January 6, 2022.</ref> See also {{ill|Okagami#Facilities|ja|岡上#施設}} and {{ill|History of Okagami Village|ja|岡上村#歴史|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. * Okagami Shrine (おかがみじんじゃ) - The former name of {{ill|Okanomiya Shrine (Fukaya City)|ja|岡廼宮神社 (深谷市)|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, located in {{ill|Fukaya City|ja|深谷市|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Saitama Prefecture|ja|埼玉県|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
