e of the former {{ill|Suwa Shrine|ja|諏訪神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Suwa Shrine|qq=}} in the center of the village was chosen for the new shrine to promote unity among villagers.<ref name="Asao Tourism">[https://asao-kankou.jp/?page_id=1992 Okagami Shrine (おかがみじんじゃ)] Asao Tourism, Kawasaki/Asao Tourism Association, accessed January 6, 2022.</ref> See also {{ill|Okagami#Facilities|ja|岡上#施設|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Okagami#Facilities|qq=}} and {{ill|History of Okagami Village|ja|岡上村#歴史|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/History of Okagami Village|qq=}}. * Okagami Shrine (おかがみじんじゃ) - The former name of {{ill|Okanomiya Shrine (Fukaya City)|ja|岡廼宮神社 (深谷市)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Okanomiya Shrine (Fukaya City)|qq=}}, located in {{ill|Fukaya City|ja|深谷市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fukaya City|qq=}}, {{ill|Saitama Prefecture|ja|埼玉県|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Saitama Prefecture|qq=}}.
