'''Okanoue Shrine''' (おかのうえじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|WD=Q845945}} enshrined in {{ill|lt=Itano, Tokushima|Q1350904|WD=Q1350904}}, {{ill|lt=Tokushima Prefecture|Q160734|WD=Q160734}}.

=== History ===
Its year of foundation is unknown. It is a {{ill||lt=Shikinaisha|UNKNOWN}} listed in the ''{{ill|lt=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|Q11064932|WD=Q11064932}}''. In {{ill|lt=1789|Q7772|WD=Q7772}} (Kansei 1), it moved to the current site.

It is said that {{ill|lt=Minamoto no Yoshitsune|Q310445|WD=Q310445}} worshipped here and prayed for lasting military fortune while heading from landing at Katsuura in {{ill|lt=Awa Province|Q907457|WD=Q907457}} to {{ill|lt=Yashima|Q11465681|WD=Q11465681}} in {{ill|lt=Sanuki Province|Q929682|WD=Q929682}}. There is also a theory that "Okanoue" was originally read "Okanokami," and is a corruption of "Uka no kami."

Within the precincts stands a {{ill|lt=camphor tree|Q158722|WD=Q158722}} called "Ōkusu of Okanomiya," designated a Tokushima Prefectural Natural Monument. It has long been called the "Sacred Mirror Tree." With a girth of about 25 m, its trunk splits from one root into three, and one of those splits again, so four trunks stand side by side as if pressing against each other.

=== Enshrined deity ===
* {{ill|lt=Toyouke-hime|Q2983724|WD=Q2983724|lt=Toyouke-hime-no-Mikoto}}

=== Precinct shrine ===
* Jisha Shrine

=== Access ===
* About 5 minutes by car from {{ill|lt=Itano Interchange|Q11105197|WD=Q11105197}} on the {{ill|lt=Tokushima Expressway|Q11490216|WD=Q11490216}}.
* About 10 minutes on foot from {{ill|lt=Itano Station|Q8190673|WD=Q8190673}} on the {{ill|lt=Kōtoku Line|Q859984|WD=Q859984}} of {{ill|lt=JR Shikoku|Q496531|WD=Q496531|lt=JR}}.

=== References ===
* ''{{ill|lt=Kadokawa Nihon Chimei Daijiten|Q4093011|WD=Q4093011}} 36 Tokushima Prefecture'' ({{ill|lt=1986|Q2430|WD=Q2430}} ISBN 4040013603)

